name: Pineal Paradise Hoodies
description:
Coming soon! We are in the final stages of releasing my original Pineal Paradise designs on hoodies, we are hopeful that we will be posting up the PreOrder options within the first two weeks of January 2014 and that orders will be sent out come mid to late February 2014 if things go as planned. In the meantime, we could get things moving along a little quicker if you participated in our poll below. This way we can get an idea of what folks are most interested in before we even have the samples and an order can be placed sooner! Thank you for your input!
Loading web poll...

Final cost is to be determined. The more that are ordered initially, the lower the cost will be. We are thinking somewhere between $100-$130 shipped, could be less though if we get the word spread and more orders placed!

name: "Come Together" Tank Top
description: This particular 'unisexy' Tank Top features the artwork "Come Together" [Detailed description of artwork available upon request] We realize that everyone has a different shape and prefer a different fit in clothing so we are offering our Shirts in sizes 2X-Small through 5X-Large. Tank Tops are a slimmer fit than the men's Tees. Kid Sizes are also available upon special request. Sizing is fairly standard, if you have further questions please see our Size Chart posted on this website. These shirts are printed using a new technique called Dye Sublimation Printing allowing for maximum image quality. This process requires the use of a Polyester material, but not the kind of polyester your grandparents are used to. This polyester is a breathable material and is actually the same material used for many athletic jerseys allowing the shirt to dry in minutes. The best part about these shirts are all the things they do not do! They do not fade, crack, shrink, or wrinkle! Great for throwing in your pack and pulling on when the sun is the hottest and your nights are the longest. --For the Holiday rush, Pre-Orders will be placed to our factory in batches every week. Orders generally take 3-4 weeks to be finished and shipped to us. We will then package and ship out all orders as soon as we receive them. Shipping via USPS takes from 2-7* days, delays should be taken into consideration due to the high amount of gifts being sent for the holidays. *within in the continental US. [Custom designs available upon serious request!]

I've always been an admirer of Dima's work from the first time I saw the flyer for The Werks first Werk Out. Now after many years I finally had the opportunity to work with him on this cosmically conscious focused shirt, you just might recognize the work from the official Gratifly Festival poster. name: ARTIST SERIES: Misha Esterkin  Tshirt
description: This particular T-shirt features the artwork of Misha Esterkin As I walked down the campground shakedown at Electric Forest I gave my usual smile, wave, and a wink as I passed by my friends at the Subliminal Tactix booth, but that day I had to quickly take a few steps back. I was completely caught off guard by the wonderful newness I spotted front and center in the booth and had to go back to pick my jaw up off the dusty path. After swooning over the piece and having meet the artist I just had to ask if he wanted to be apart of the Artist Series and here we are today! I can't wait to see what other magic Misha comes up with in his Biomorphism. He's actually a jack-of-all-trades, master-of-many, when it comes to the Art world so I'm sure we will be left nothing short of breathless. name: ARTIST SERIES: Bonnie Goodson  Tshirt
description: This particular T-shirt features the artwork of Bonnie Goodson From the first time I laid eyes on Bonnie's work I was just speechless, being a digital artist I couldn't wrap my mind around her effortlessly flowing brushstrokes. It was a pleasure to work with her pieces "Spiral Out" and "Frisco", two of my favorites of hers'. The unfolding of this collaboration happened so fast and fluently, once I got the files that is! I look forward to working with her again and again so keep your eyes peeled for more collaborations between Miss Bonnie and I! name: ARTIST SERIES: Nick Hamann Tshirt
description: This particular T-shirt features the artwork of Nick Hamann I have always admired Nick's HDR Fine Art Photography and his use of fractals within his images. It is as if his lens opens up a porthole to the 'other side'. I had Nick send me a couple images he had shot of a beach on the East Coast near his home and a few fractal images he had created. I pieced together four of his photos and placed two of his fractals strategically to create this spectacularly surreal sunset! description:

Antique Copper [Shown]

This pin represents the Big Bang and the expansion of the Universe, or multi-verse if you will. It features the partial pattern of the Flower of Life stamped into the three dimensional form of an egg. Here the egg shape symbolizes the beginning and fertile state of our newly formed universe and all of its infinite possibilities. 

We have chosen to offer it in an antique copper finish to add yet another meaning behind this pin. Here the copper egg is representing Tesla's Egg of Columbus where he placed a copper egg in the center of a rotating magnetic field causing the egg to spin on end thus demonstrating the principles of the induction motor.
